<br>
Take a level 60 warrior with 1500+ AC and tank a decaying skeleton and log the hit %. Now have that same warrior tank a decaying skeleton naked. You will see the hit % is the same.<br>
<br>
Mitigation is exactly that. It mitigates a successful hit, it doesn't eliminate it. That is something called avoidance, which is composed of defensive skill, AGI, and level. There is a reason why we have the term &quot;minimum hit&quot;. If a mob successfully overcomes your avoidance, you will take the minimum amount of damage. <p>Graal MacBladefury<BR>
