<br>
To add something:<br>
&quot;Miss rate is clearly not a function of level difference - kromrif recruiter at the EW entrance to Kael is level 1 and hits me (level 49) about 68% percent of the time.&quot;<br>
<br>
It is and it isn't; technically you're right.  For PCs, levels = weapon/offense skill points = ATK.  Therefore levels means higher ATK.  MOBs don't follow this rule since they are assigned an ATK rating; so level really doesn't mean anything to them.  Just with MOBs level is generally consistant with ATK, but not always so  (as in the above Recruiter case).<br>
<br>
