<br>
ie: I tested baton of faith versus strength of grodan while soloing self buffed in velks. The baton of faith outperformed the strength of grodan by about a 20% margin. Neither weapon proc's and I did not have self proc buff loaded. Str of grodan has both a better ratio overall and a higher dmg bonus(plus str).<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujoimster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Joimster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 6:20:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1242.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ubermob tanking</span><hr size=1> I did a quick test with damage mitigation against &quot;a young kodiak&quot; in WC:<br>
I'd like to redo this test for a longer amount of time, perhaps against a higher ATK mob, for better numbers.<br>
<br>
I'm a level 49 Paladin.<br>
Naked, I'm at 571 AC.<br>
Wearing all my armor that didn't have +AGI (which would add to avoidance AC), my AC was 932.<br>
This young kodiak had a max hit of 22.<br>
<br>
Naked, he swung 196 times, missed me 173 times, that's 88.3% misses. Average damage on a hit was 13.2.<br>
<br>
With armor, he swung 225 times, missed 180 times, that's 80.0% misses. Average damage on a hit was 4.0.<br>
<br>
If we assume that the actual (with an infinite number of swings) miss rate is right in the middle, we can say that each of these measured miss rates had a probability of less than 10% for being this far away from the actual rate.<br>
Sorry if that was confusing, I'm trying to make complicated statistics sound simple. Basically, we are more than 90% confident that these rates are individually not 84% misses.<br>
<br>
Hmm, we seem to conclude that either the random number generator is trash, or my armor made him miss me LESS often. This is the opposite of mitigation of hits into misses, wonder where I ever read about that in the first place. Is it because my armor added to my weight when I took it out of my WR bags? Thought that was only monks. Didn't think to check my weight while doing these tests.<br>
<br>
As I said, I'd like to get some longer logs against a higher ATK mob.<br>
<br>
An interesting side note: The damage distribution against me while I was naked seemed to be approximately uniform. I would think this is true because my mitigation AC while naked was zero, and the young kodiak's ATK was close to zero also. I might guess that equal mitigation AC and mob ATK would give a uniform distribution of damage.<br>
<br>
These are just some preliminary ideas from a short (few minutes) tanking session - take them with a grain of salt.<br>
<br>
- Joim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufarmatyr1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>farmatyr1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 7:11:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1242.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ubermob tanking</span><hr size=1> I'm more concerned with how much damage I do, because this is something I have control over. My question is: is max damage inherent in the weapon, or can ATK affect it? It seems to me that my max, not just average, damage goes up when I increase my ATK, but this could also be explained by a very low chance of hitting at the high end of the scale, but I think using a 29/41 weapon, damage bonus 19, modal damage 77, I have hit for 154 max. Assuming that the 77 is 20 * DI + 19, that gives DI of 2.9, so 40*DI + bonus is 135.<br>
